<div id="subject_distribution" class="section level4">
<h4>Distribution</h4>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">show_missing_values &lt;- <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (has_labels(item)) {
  missing_values &lt;- item[is.na(haven::zap_missing(item))]
  attributes(missing_values) &lt;- attributes(item)
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!is.null(attributes(item)$labels)) {
    attributes(missing_values)$labels &lt;- attributes(missing_values)$labels[is.na(attributes(missing_values)$labels)]
    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;
  (exists(<span class="hljs-string">"type"</span>, item_info) &amp;&amp; 
    any(stringr::str_detect(item_info$type, 
                            pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">"multiple"</span>))))
  ) {
  item_nomiss &lt;- unlist(stringr::str_split(item_nomiss, pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>)))
}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>
go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels
  
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {
  <span class="hljs-comment"># numeric items are plotted horizontally (because that's what usually expected)</span>
  <span class="hljs-comment"># categorical items are plotted vertically because we can use the screen real estate better this way</span>

    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.null(choices) || 
        dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss) &gt; length(non_missing_choices)) {
        non_missing_choices &lt;- unique(item_nomiss)
        names(non_missing_choices) &lt;- non_missing_choices
    }
  choice_multiplier &lt;- old_height/<span class="hljs-number">6.5</span>
    new_height &lt;- <span class="hljs-number">2</span> + choice_multiplier * length(non_missing_choices)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &gt; <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, new_height)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &lt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, new_height)
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp; is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      new_height &lt;- old_height
    }
    knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.height = new_height)
}

wrap_at &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.width"</span>) * <span class="hljs-number">10</span></code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-comment"># todo: if there are free-text choices mingled in with the pre-defined ones, don't show</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: show rare items if they are pre-defined</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: bin rare responses into "other category"</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!length(item_nomiss)) {
  cat(<span class="hljs-string">"No non-missing values to show."</span>)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss)) {
  plot_labelled(item_nomiss, item_name, wrap_at, go_vertical)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      char_count &lt;- stringr::str_count(item_nomiss)
      attributes(char_count)$label &lt;- item_label
      plot_labelled(char_count, 
                    item_name, wrap_at, <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>, trans = <span class="hljs-string">"log1p"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"characters"</span>)
  } <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
      cat(dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss), <span class="hljs-string">" unique, categorical values, so not shown."</span>)
  }
}</code></pre>

  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {

item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (

attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]

  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {

    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)

  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {

  }

item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;

}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>

<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {

<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">show_missing_values &lt;- <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (has_labels(item)) {
  missing_values &lt;- item[is.na(haven::zap_missing(item))]
  attributes(missing_values) &lt;- attributes(item)
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!is.null(attributes(item)$labels)) {
    attributes(missing_values)$labels &lt;- attributes(missing_values)$labels[is.na(attributes(missing_values)$labels)]
    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;
  (exists(<span class="hljs-string">"type"</span>, item_info) &amp;&amp; 
    any(stringr::str_detect(item_info$type, 
                            pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">"multiple"</span>))))
  ) {
  item_nomiss &lt;- unlist(stringr::str_split(item_nomiss, pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>)))
}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>
go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels
  
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {
  <span class="hljs-comment"># numeric items are plotted horizontally (because that's what usually expected)</span>
  <span class="hljs-comment"># categorical items are plotted vertically because we can use the screen real estate better this way</span>

    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.null(choices) || 
        dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss) &gt; length(non_missing_choices)) {
        non_missing_choices &lt;- unique(item_nomiss)
        names(non_missing_choices) &lt;- non_missing_choices
    }
  choice_multiplier &lt;- old_height/<span class="hljs-number">6.5</span>
    new_height &lt;- <span class="hljs-number">2</span> + choice_multiplier * length(non_missing_choices)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &gt; <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, new_height)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &lt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, new_height)
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp; is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      new_height &lt;- old_height
    }
    knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.height = new_height)
}

wrap_at &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.width"</span>) * <span class="hljs-number">10</span></code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-comment"># todo: if there are free-text choices mingled in with the pre-defined ones, don't show</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: show rare items if they are pre-defined</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: bin rare responses into "other category"</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!length(item_nomiss)) {
  cat(<span class="hljs-string">"No non-missing values to show."</span>)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss)) {
  plot_labelled(item_nomiss, item_name, wrap_at, go_vertical)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {

                    item_name, wrap_at, <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>, trans = <span class="hljs-string">"log1p"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"characters"</span>)
  } <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
      cat(dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss), <span class="hljs-string">" unique, categorical values, so not shown."</span>)
  }
}</code></pre>

item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (

attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]

    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]

  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;
  (exists(<span class="hljs-string">"type"</span>, item_info) &amp;&amp; 
    any(stringr::str_detect(item_info$type, 
                            pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">"multiple"</span>))))
  ) {
  item_nomiss &lt;- unlist(stringr::str_split(item_nomiss, pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>)))
}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>
go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels
  
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {
  <span class="hljs-comment"># numeric items are plotted horizontally (because that's what usually expected)</span>

  }

<div id="timeBodyGyroscope_std___X" class="section level3 tabset">
<h3>timeBodyGyroscope-std()-X</h3>
<div id="timeBodyGyroscope_std___X_distribution" class="section level4">
<h4>Distribution</h4>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">show_missing_values &lt;- <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (has_labels(item)) {
  missing_values &lt;- item[is.na(haven::zap_missing(item))]
  attributes(missing_values) &lt;- attributes(item)
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!is.null(attributes(item)$labels)) {
    attributes(missing_values)$labels &lt;- attributes(missing_values)$labels[is.na(attributes(missing_values)$labels)]
    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;
  (exists(<span class="hljs-string">"type"</span>, item_info) &amp;&amp; 
    any(stringr::str_detect(item_info$type, 
                            pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">"multiple"</span>))))
  ) {
  item_nomiss &lt;- unlist(stringr::str_split(item_nomiss, pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>)))
}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>
go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels
  
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {
  <span class="hljs-comment"># numeric items are plotted horizontally (because that's what usually expected)</span>
  <span class="hljs-comment"># categorical items are plotted vertically because we can use the screen real estate better this way</span>

    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.null(choices) || 
        dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss) &gt; length(non_missing_choices)) {
        non_missing_choices &lt;- unique(item_nomiss)
        names(non_missing_choices) &lt;- non_missing_choices
    }
  choice_multiplier &lt;- old_height/<span class="hljs-number">6.5</span>
    new_height &lt;- <span class="hljs-number">2</span> + choice_multiplier * length(non_missing_choices)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &gt; <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, new_height)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &lt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, new_height)
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp; is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      new_height &lt;- old_height
    }
    knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.height = new_height)
}

wrap_at &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.width"</span>) * <span class="hljs-number">10</span></code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-comment"># todo: if there are free-text choices mingled in with the pre-defined ones, don't show</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: show rare items if they are pre-defined</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: bin rare responses into "other category"</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!length(item_nomiss)) {
  cat(<span class="hljs-string">"No non-missing values to show."</span>)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss)) {
  plot_labelled(item_nomiss, item_name, wrap_at, go_vertical)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      char_count &lt;- stringr::str_count(item_nomiss)
      attributes(char_count)$label &lt;- item_label
      plot_labelled(char_count, 
                    item_name, wrap_at, <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>, trans = <span class="hljs-string">"log1p"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"characters"</span>)
  } <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
      cat(dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss), <span class="hljs-string">" unique, categorical values, so not shown."</span>)
  }
}</code></pre>

<div id="timeBodyGyroscopeJerk_mean___X" class="section level3 tabset">
<h3>timeBodyGyroscopeJerk-mean()-X</h3>
<div id="timeBodyGyroscopeJerk_mean___X_distribution" class="section level4">
<h4>Distribution</h4>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">show_missing_values &lt;- <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (has_labels(item)) {
  missing_values &lt;- item[is.na(haven::zap_missing(item))]
  attributes(missing_values) &lt;- attributes(item)
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!is.null(attributes(item)$labels)) {
    attributes(missing_values)$labels &lt;- attributes(missing_values)$labels[is.na(attributes(missing_values)$labels)]
    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;
  (exists(<span class="hljs-string">"type"</span>, item_info) &amp;&amp; 
    any(stringr::str_detect(item_info$type, 
                            pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">"multiple"</span>))))
  ) {
  item_nomiss &lt;- unlist(stringr::str_split(item_nomiss, pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>)))
}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>
go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels
  
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {
  <span class="hljs-comment"># numeric items are plotted horizontally (because that's what usually expected)</span>
  <span class="hljs-comment"># categorical items are plotted vertically because we can use the screen real estate better this way</span>

    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.null(choices) || 
        dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss) &gt; length(non_missing_choices)) {
        non_missing_choices &lt;- unique(item_nomiss)
        names(non_missing_choices) &lt;- non_missing_choices
    }
  choice_multiplier &lt;- old_height/<span class="hljs-number">6.5</span>
    new_height &lt;- <span class="hljs-number">2</span> + choice_multiplier * length(non_missing_choices)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &gt; <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, new_height)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &lt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, new_height)
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp; is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      new_height &lt;- old_height
    }
    knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.height = new_height)
}

wrap_at &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.width"</span>) * <span class="hljs-number">10</span></code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-comment"># todo: if there are free-text choices mingled in with the pre-defined ones, don't show</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: show rare items if they are pre-defined</span>
<span class="hljs-comment"># todo: bin rare responses into "other category"</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!length(item_nomiss)) {
  cat(<span class="hljs-string">"No non-missing values to show."</span>)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss)) {
  plot_labelled(item_nomiss, item_name, wrap_at, go_vertical)
} <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      char_count &lt;- stringr::str_count(item_nomiss)
      attributes(char_count)$label &lt;- item_label
      plot_labelled(char_count, 
                    item_name, wrap_at, <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>, trans = <span class="hljs-string">"log1p"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"characters"</span>)
  } <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
      cat(dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss), <span class="hljs-string">" unique, categorical values, so not shown."</span>)
  }
}</code></pre>

    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]

  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]

go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels

  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!is.null(attributes(item)$labels)) {
    attributes(missing_values)$labels &lt;- attributes(missing_values)$labels[is.na(attributes(missing_values)$labels)]
    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]

<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">show_missing_values &lt;- <span class="hljs-literal">FALSE</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (has_labels(item)) {

  attributes(missing_values) &lt;- attributes(item)
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (!is.null(attributes(item)$labels)) {
    attributes(missing_values)$labels &lt;- attributes(missing_values)$labels[is.na(attributes(missing_values)$labels)]
    attributes(item)$labels &lt;- attributes(item)$labels[!is.na(attributes(item)$labels)]
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.double(item)) {
    show_missing_values &lt;- length(unique(haven::na_tag(missing_values))) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>
    item &lt;- haven::zap_missing(item)
  }
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (length(item_attributes$labels) == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> &amp;&amp; is.numeric(item)) {
    item &lt;- haven::zap_labels(item)
  }
}
item_nomiss &lt;- item[!is.na(item)]

<span class="hljs-comment"># unnest mc_multiple and so on</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (
  is.character(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp;
  any(stringr::str_detect(item_nomiss, stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>))) &amp;&amp;
  !is.null(item_info) &amp;&amp;
  (exists(<span class="hljs-string">"type"</span>, item_info) &amp;&amp; 
    any(stringr::str_detect(item_info$type, 
                            pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">"multiple"</span>))))
  ) {
  item_nomiss &lt;- unlist(stringr::str_split(item_nomiss, pattern = stringr::fixed(<span class="hljs-string">", "</span>)))
}
attributes(item_nomiss) &lt;- attributes(item)

old_height &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.height"</span>)
non_missing_choices &lt;- item_attributes[[<span class="hljs-string">"labels"</span>]]
many_labels &lt;- length(non_missing_choices) &gt; <span class="hljs-number">7</span>
go_vertical &lt;- !is_numeric_or_time_var(item_nomiss) || many_labels
  
<span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> ( go_vertical ) {
  <span class="hljs-comment"># numeric items are plotted horizontally (because that's what usually expected)</span>
  <span class="hljs-comment"># categorical items are plotted vertically because we can use the screen real estate better this way</span>

    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.null(choices) || 
        dplyr::n_distinct(item_nomiss) &gt; length(non_missing_choices)) {
        non_missing_choices &lt;- unique(item_nomiss)
        names(non_missing_choices) &lt;- non_missing_choices
    }
  choice_multiplier &lt;- old_height/<span class="hljs-number">6.5</span>
    new_height &lt;- <span class="hljs-number">2</span> + choice_multiplier * length(non_missing_choices)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &gt; <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, <span class="hljs-number">20</span>, new_height)
    new_height &lt;- ifelse(new_height &lt; <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, new_height)
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(could_disclose_unique_values(item_nomiss) &amp;&amp; is.character(item_nomiss)) {
      new_height &lt;- old_height
    }
    knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.height = new_height)
}

wrap_at &lt;- knitr::opts_chunk$get(<span class="hljs-string">"fig.width"</span>) * <span class="hljs-number">10</span></code></pre>
